        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-09-28 16:05:00.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 7:\n\nThough I can't reproduce it locally, seems there is some piece missed in the osp landing: osp do create \"osc\" proc dir for the compatibility on module init, and try to remove the dir on module exit. So the when the osc module exit, it should use the 'try' mode to remove the \"osc\" entry as well. See the changes in class_unregister_type(). Thank you, Oleg.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 7
    },
